nd ruler of the United Arab Emirates Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum, Gabonese president Ali Bongo Ondimba, Lebanese prime minister Najib Mikati, Ecuadorian president Guillermo Lasso and the King of Jordan King Abdullah II.";}i:2;i:1047;}i:29;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:1654;}i:30;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:1654;}i:31;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:524:"According to the ICIJ, a notable purchase of a $22 million chateau in the French Riviera purchased through offshore companies by the Czech Republic’s populist prime minister, Andrej Babis a billionaire who has railed against the corruption of economic and political elites. Furthermore, three beachfront mansions in Malibu purchased through three offshore companies for $68 million by the King of Jordan Abdullah II in the years after Jordanians filled the streets during Arab Spring to protest joblessness and corruption.";}i:2;i:1656;}i:32;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2180;}i:33;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"section_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2182;}i:34;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"header";i:1;a:3:{i:0;s:19:"Effects of the leak";i:1;i:3;i:2;i:2182;}i:2;i:2182;}i:35;a:3:{i:0;s:12:"section_open";i:1;a:1:{i:0;i:3;}i:2;i:2182;}i:36;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2182;}i:37;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:362:"Days after the leak, the controversy of the Pandora Papers resulted in Czech citizens voting Andrej Babis out of office. Babis's party finished second in a national plebiscite, narrowly losing the election and putting Babis out of office. One media poll suggested 8% of his party’s supporters switched their votes as a result of the Pandora Papers disclosures.";}i:2;i:2213;}i:38;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2575;}i:39;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2575;}i:40;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:317:"U.S. lawmakers have also pushed for legislation known as the Enablers act that would force trust companies, lawyers, art dealers and others seeking to transfer and move money and assets into the A